    <div class="card">
      <h1>07 — Faith, Confessions & Victory</h1>
      <p><b>Goal:</b> To understand Bible faith and the power of spoken confession grounded in God’s Word.</p>

      <h2>Key Scriptures</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Romans 10:17</b> — Faith comes by hearing the Word of God.</li>
        <li><b>Mark 11:23</b> — Speak to the mountain and do not doubt.</li>
        <li><b>Proverbs 18:21</b> — Life and death are in the power of the tongue.</li>
        <li><b>2 Corinthians 4:13</b> — “We believe, therefore we speak.”</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Truths to Note</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Confession is not noise — it is agreement with God’s Word.</li>
        <li>Faith must be fed daily; doubt grows where Word is absent.</li>
        <li>Speak what God says, while you do what God commands.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Practice This Week</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Write 5 scriptures for your situation; confess them morning and night.</li>
        <li>Replace complaints with declarations of faith.</li>
        <li>Take one obedient action that matches your confession.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Prayer Points</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Lord, increase my faith and establish me in Your Word.</li>
        <li>I receive grace to speak rightly and refuse fear.</li>
        <li>Every contrary voice against my destiny, be silenced in Jesus’ Name.</li>
      </ul>

